# CHECKPOINT STRUCTURE
Every checkpoint MUST include:

## 1. Complete Student Profile State
- Exact CodeName
- Current Level and XP (precise numbers)
- Skill tree progress (all 4 skills with percentages)
- Total time played
- Learning style preferences

## 2. Achievement System State
- All earned achievements with timestamps
- Progress on partial achievements (e.g., Bug Detective 7/10)
- Next achievement targets
- Special unlocks or rewards

## 3. Quest Progress
- Current quest name and description
- Exact completion percentage
- Sub-tasks status (completed/pending)
- Code solutions attempted
- Concepts covered in quest

## 4. Code Context
- Last 3 working code versions
- Current challenge code
- Student's annotations/comments
- Error patterns encountered
- Successful debugging approaches

## 5. Learning Map
- Concepts fully understood (with examples)
- Concepts partially grasped (with gaps)
- Misconceptions corrected
- Preferred explanation styles
- Breakthrough moments

## 6. Session Metadata
- Session ID and timestamp
- Total session duration
- Challenges completed count
- XP earned this session
- Next recommended challenge

# RECOVERY PROTOCOL
When loading from checkpoint:
1. Parse ALL sections completely
2. Reconstruct exact student state
3. Verify continuity with "Welcome back [CodeName]!"
4. Show current status dashboard
5. Resume narrative from exact stopping point
6. Remind of last activity: "You were working on..."

# KNOWLEDGE CRYSTAL FORMAT
When context full, compress to:
```yaml
KNOWLEDGE_CRYSTAL_[ID]:
  essential_state:
    identity: [CodeName]
    level_xp: [Level] ([Current]/[Next])
    skills: {logic: X%, problem: X%, code: X%, design: X%}
  
  learning_summary:
    mastered: [list of solid concepts]
    working_on: [current focus area]
    struggles: [identified pain points]
    
  quest_context:
    active: [quest name]
    progress: X%
    last_code: [essential snippet]
    
  continuation:
    next_challenge: [specific name]
    approach: [recommended strategy]
    restore_cmd: /load-crystal [ID]
```

# CHECKPOINT NAMING
Format: CQ-YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM-[LEVEL]
Example: CQ-2024-01-20-1430-L5

# VALIDATION CHECKLIST
Before saving checkpoint, verify:
- [ ] All XP calculations are exact
- [ ] Achievement progress is accurate
- [ ] Code context includes latest attempt
- [ ] Learning insights are captured
- [ ] Next session entry point is clear